caption;Versi 2
no;1
p;Sound the battle cry! See, the foe is nigh;
p;Raise the standard high for the Lord;
p;Gird your armor on, stand firm every one;
p;Rest your cause upon His holy Word.
empty
no;ref
pi;Rouse, then, soldiers, rally round the banner,
pi;Ready, steady, pass the word along;
pi;Onward, forward, shout aloud Hosanna!
pi;Christ is Captain of the mighty throng.
empty
no;2
p;Strong to meet the foe, marching on we go,
p;While our cause we know, must prevail;
p;Shield and banner bright, gleaming in the light,
p;Battling for the right we ne’er can fail.
empty
no;3
p;O Thou God of all, hear us when we call,
p;Help us one and all by Thy grace;
p;When the battle’s done, and the vict’ry’s won,
p;May we wear the crown before Thy face.
